ingredients.ingredient: 1 pound butternut squash - peeled, seeded, and cut into thick French fries
¼ teaspoon ground black pepper, or to taste
½ teaspoon Cajun seasoning, or to taste

cookingTips: Cut squash into uniform thickness for even cooking; aim for ½-¾ inch thick
Spray baking sheet well and arrange fries in single layer without crowding
Bake at 425°F for 25-35 minutes, stirring halfway through, until crispy and golden
enrichment.coachingPrompt: These are a healthier alternative to potato fries. Do you have Cajun seasoning, or would you like to make your own blend?
